        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 6 at 6:29PM PDT by NWS Spokane WA</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 22
miles southeast of Nespelem Community, or 49 miles southeast of Omak,
moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern
Lincoln and southwestern Ferry Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
